      "id": "IC_kwDOIvux3s8AAAABKSUUMg",
      "body": "<h3>Greptile Summary</h3>\n\nThis PR adds declarative `[bootstrap.plugins]` support and `mise bootstrap plugins apply|status` commands, allowing users to declare package-manager plugins (vscode extensions, helm plugins, etc.) that are installed before `mise install` runs and whose packages are applied after tools are available.\n\n- Adds `BootstrapPart::Plugins` and splits the package phase into built-in packages (step 1) and plugin-managed packages (step 9.5), with `apply_bootstrap_plugins` extracted and called first in the orchestration loop.\n- Extracts `install_plugin` as `pub(crate)` with a built-in-name collision guard; removes the fixed `value_parser` enum from `--manager` to allow dynamic plugin names; improves unknown-manager warnings with install hints.\n- Adds docs, JSON schema, man page, KDL usage spec, and E2E coverage for the full plugin lifecycle.\n\n<h3>Confidence Score: 4/5</h3>\n\nSafe to merge after addressing the post-packages hook timing regression.\n\nThe PostPackages hook unconditionally runs at step 9.5 (after mise install, repos, dotfiles, shell activation, etc.) even for configs with zero plugin packages. Before this PR it ran immediately after built-in package installation. Any existing user with a post-packages hook will silently see it run far later in the sequence.\n\nsrc/cli/bootstrap.rs \u2014 the plugin-packages block at lines 757-780 runs PostPackages unconditionally; review whether it should be guarded by plugin-package presence or moved back for configs with no plugin packages.\n\n<h3>Important Files Changed</h3>\n\n\n\n\n| Filename | Overview |\n|----------|----------|\n| src/cli/bootstrap.rs | Core bootstrap orchestration: adds plugin installation at step 0, splits package phase into built-in (step 1) and plugin (step 9.5), but unconditionally moves PostPackages hook to step 9.5 \u2014 a silent ordering regression for all post-packages hook users |\n| src/cli/plugins/install.rs | Extracts install_plugin as a pub(crate) function; adds built-in manager name collision guard and dry_run pass-through |\n| src/system/mod.rs | Adds plugins field to BootstrapTomlConfig and plugins_from_config helper; logic is correct |\n| e2e/plugins/test_package_plugin | New E2E test covering status, apply, version pins, requires binary, full-bootstrap self-provisioning, and built-in name collision rejection |\n| src/cli/system/install.rs | Removes the fixed value_parser enum from --manager to allow dynamic plugin names |\n| src/cli/system/upgrade.rs | Same --manager constraint removal as install.rs |\n| schema/mise.json | Adds bootstrap.plugins schema entry; straightforward addition |\n\n\n<!-- greptile_other_comments_section -->\n\n<sub>Reviews (2): Last reviewed commit: [\"fix(bootstrap): await plugin package ava...\"](https://github.com/jdx/mise/commit/e9c3c67142a496a638aa773c6e6ae1b5cc01733e) | [Re-trigger Greptile](https://app.greptile.com/api/retrigger?id=44612555)</sub>",
