            "body": "<a href=\"#\"><img alt=\"P2\" src=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/p2.svg?v=9\" align=\"top\"></a> **`\"Use --force to install anyway\"` hint removed from `plugin install`**\n\nThe refactor dropped the second `warn!` that told users how to overcome the already-installed guard. Before this PR, `mise plugin install foo` when `foo` was already present emitted \"Plugin foo already installed\" followed by \"Use --force to install anyway\". Now only the first message fires, leaving users without actionable guidance when they want to update or reinstall.\n\n<a href=\"https://app.greptile.com/ide/claude-code?prompt=This%20is%20a%20comment%20left%20during%20a%20code%20review.%0APath%3A%20src%2Fcli%2Fplugins%2Finstall.rs%0ALine%3A%20158-160%0A%0AComment%3A%0A**%60%22Use%20--force%20to%20install%20anyway%22%60%20hint%20removed%20from%20%60plugin%20install%60**%0A%0AThe%20refactor%20dropped%20the%20second%20%60warn!%60%20that%20told%20users%20how%20to%20overcome%20the%20already-installed%20guard.%20Before%20this%20PR%2C%20%60mise%20plugin%20install%20foo%60%20when%20%60foo%60%20was%20already%20present%20emitted%20%22Plugin%20foo%20already%20installed%22%20followed%20by%20%22Use%20--force%20to%20install%20anyway%22.%20Now%20only%20the%20first%20message%20fires%2C%20leaving%20users%20without%20actionable%20guidance%20when%20they%20want%20to%20update%20or%20reinstall.%0A%0AHow%20can%20I%20resolve%20this%3F%20If%20you%20propose%20a%20fix%2C%20please%20make%20it%20concise.&repo=jdx%2Fmise&pr=11024&platform=github\"><picture><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixInClaudeDark.svg?v=6\"><source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixInClaude.svg?v=6\"><img alt=\"Fix in Claude Code\" src=\"https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/FixInClaude.svg?v=6\"></picture></a>",
